Key Match Events: Ben Stokes scored 108 runs in 84 balls for his first World Cup ton
Adil Rashid claimed 3-54 and Moeen Ali bagged 3-42 in spin bowling
The Netherlands was all out for 179 runs
Post-Match Reflections: Ben Stokes said, 'It's been a tough World Cup and it's nice to get back on winning terms today.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: England snapped its five-match losing streak
The Dutch stemmed the flow of runs with wickets, removing Harry Brook and an out-of-form Buttler
England added 124 runs in the last 10 overs to finish strongly
